{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.25",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 25,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 25 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:1",
      "text": "These also are proverbs of Solomon which the men of Hezekiah king of Judah copied.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:2",
      "text": "It is the glory of God to conceal things, but the glory of kings is to search things out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:3",
      "text": "As the heavens for height, and the earth for depth, so the mind of kings is unsearchable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:4",
      "text": "Take away the dross from the silver, and the smith has material for a vessel;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:5",
      "text": "take away the wicked from the presence of the king, and his throne will be established in righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:6",
      "text": "Do not put yourself forward in the king's presence or stand in the place of the great;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:7",
      "text": "for it is better to be told, “Come up here,” than to be put lower in the presence of the prince. What your eyes have seen",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:8",
      "text": "do not hastily bring into court; for what will you do in the end, when your neighbor puts you to shame?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:9",
      "text": "Argue your case with your neighbor himself, and do not disclose another's secret;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:10",
      "text": "lest he who hears you bring shame upon you, and your ill repute have no end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:11",
      "text": "A word fitly spoken is like apples of gold in a setting of silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:12",
      "text": "Like a gold ring or an ornament of gold is a wise reprover to a listening ear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:13",
      "text": "Like the cold of snow in the time of harvest is a faithful messenger to those who send him, he refreshes the spirit of his masters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:14",
      "text": "Like clouds and wind without rain is a man who boasts of a gift he does not give.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:15",
      "text": "With patience a ruler may be persuaded, and a soft tongue will break a bone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:16",
      "text": "If you have found honey, eat only enough for you, lest you be sated with it and vomit it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:17",
      "text": "Let your foot be seldom in your neighbor's house, lest he become weary of you and hate you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:18",
      "text": "A man who bears false witness against his neighbor is like a war club, or a sword, or a sharp arrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:19",
      "text": "Trust in a faithless man in time of trouble is like a bad tooth or a foot that slips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:20",
      "text": "He who sings songs to a heavy heart is like one who takes off a garment on a cold day, and like vinegar on a wound.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:21",
      "text": "If your enemy is hungry, give him bread to eat; and if he is thirsty, give him water to drink;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:22",
      "text": "for you will heap coals of fire on his head, and the Lord will reward you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:23",
      "text": "The north wind brings forth rain; and a backbiting tongue, angry looks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:24",
      "text": "It is better to live in a corner of the housetop than in a house shared with a contentious woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:25",
      "text": "Like cold water to a thirsty soul, so is good news from a far country.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:26",
      "text": "Like a muddied spring or a polluted fountain is a righteous man who gives way before the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:27",
      "text": "It is not good to eat much honey, so be sparing of complimentary words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.25.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:28",
      "text": "A man without self-control is like a city broken into and left without walls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
